<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="450">
Etymology L 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181898" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole meinertopsis Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole meinertopsis Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="450" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meinertopsis">meinertopsis</taxonomicName>
, resembling 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33861" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole meinerti Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole meinerti Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="450" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meinerti">(Pheidole) meinerti</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="450">
diagnosis Resembling in some traits 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33861" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole meinerti Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole meinerti Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="450" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meinerti">meinerti</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181949" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tambopatae Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tambopatae Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="450" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tambopatae">tambopatae</taxonomicName>
. differing as follows.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="450">Major: reddish yellow; mesonotal convexity well developed; in dorsal-oblique view, dorsal pronotal profde bilobate, including a prominent lobose humerus; dorsal mesosomal pilosity sparse, consisting of a row of well-spaced pairs of setae; petiolar node tapers to a blunt point at apex; postpetiole from above trapezoidal; carinulae originating on frontal lobes spread outward slightly from the midline and extend to but not across the occiput.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="450">Minor: pilosity sparse, on promesonotal profde consisting of evenly spaced pairs of setae; in dorsal-oblique view, pronotal profde bilobate; the humerus and mesonotal convexity angulate; eye set well forward on head; occiput broad and strongly concave. Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 0.88, HL 0.92, SL 0.46, EL 0.12, PW 0.42. Paratype minor: HW 0.44, HL 0.46, SL 0.42, EL 0.06, PW 0.26.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="450">Color Major: body and mandibles medium reddish yellow, other appendages clear medium yellow. Minor: medium reddish yellow except for gaster and appendages, which are plain medium yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="450">Range Known only from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="450">Biology The type colony was found on the ground in terra firme forest, nesting in a rotten stick on top of leaf litter.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
